&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you an experienced pharmacist seeking a new challenge? Are you tech-savvy and have a keen interest in the use of digital solutions to improve patient safety? Do you enjoy working on exciting new projects that offer a real sense of achievement? Are you excited by the opportunity to work in a progressive pharmacy department that has a clear vision for the future? If so, then we have the role for you.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; The Lister Hospital, Stevenage is looking for a high caliber pharmacist to join our expanding team as an advanced pharmacist for electronic prescribing and medicines administration (ePMA). This is a new post which will work alongside fantastic multidisciplinary and IT teams to lead on all pharmacy aspects of the implementation of ePMA. The successful candidate will be enthusiastic, innovative and resourceful, whilst possessing a thorough clinical pharmacy knowledge which they will utilise to deliver an ePMA solution as the Trust transitions from its pilot to a full-scale roll out in 2021. Being driven and adaptable are essential characteristics for this role as this is a unique opportunity to shape the future pathway of a major Trust project as the system is fine-tuned in order to deliver key benefits and informatics advantages through maturing to &#39;business as usual.&#39; The successful candidate will sit on the Trust’s ePMA board and report directly to key stakeholders both within pharmacy and Trust senior managers.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will lead and line manage other members of the pharmacy ePMA team, and there will be a clinical commitment to the role for suitable candidates.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Continued professional development is actively supported in the pharmacy department and there will be opportunities to undertake postgraduate training / qualifications where applicable. The successful candidate will also be supported to develop their leadership and management skills.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; If this sounds like the opportunity for you, please get in touch with us!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarb Sarai, Lead Critical Care and ePMA pharmacist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address : sarb.sarai@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number : 01438 284032&lt;/p&gt;
